		<track>
			<location>file:///home/seanpm2001/Desktop/SeansLifeArchive/Extras/Audio/1%20Music/Hava-Nagila/MP3/Hava-Nagila.mp3</location>
			<title>Hava-Nagila.mp3</title>
			<creator>Idelsohn or Nathanson (disputed)</creator>
			<album>Hava Nagila</album>
			<trackNum>1</trackNum>
			<annotation>The Jewish folk song Hava Nagila. Its original creator is commonly disputed, it was either composed by Idelsohn or Nathanson. It was composed in 1918 to celebrate victory over the Ottoman Empire in World War I. The song name translates to &quot;Let us rejoice&quot; in English. I am using a picture of the sheet music as the album art, rather than the flag of Israel.</annotation>
			<image>file:///home/seanpm2001/snap/vlc/common/.cache/vlc/art/artistalbum/Idelsohn%20or%20Nathanson%20%28disputed%29/Hava%20Nagila/art.png</image>
			<duration>165233</duration>
			<extension application="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/playlist/0">
				<vlc:id>9</vlc:id>
			</extension>
		</track>
